title: fact_taxprep_session
description:
SOURCE: MATT

This table is meant to represent Taxprep sessions or session start and ends for when a user has entered the TTO Application and has the ability to interact with their tax formset.

 

session_type = 'start' is definitely when a user creates a new session with the TTO application.  Session Types will generally have a corresponding session_type = 'end' for when the application session ends.

 

There are many session_type = 'end' records in this table without a corresponding session_type 'start'.  These may be coming from a different application than TTO.

 

Use session_type = 'start' to get the MATT/Server based count of users that were active on TTO for any given period of time.  Since there are weird session_type = 'end' records in here, sessionization and counting users while including session_type = 'end' records becomes problematic.

title: Leg Type
description:
Leg type can be IVR, QUEUE or AGENT.  A traditional call starts from the IVR and progress through Queue to Agent.   If the call is transferred it can either be followed by a QUEUE leg, if transferred to a QUEUE, or to an AGENT if transferred directly to an AGENT.

Outbound calls start with the AGENT leg.

Direct to Agent calls go from IVR to AGENT and do not go through the QUEUE.

While a Scheduled Callback or Click to Call Callback do not involve a traditional IVR experience, there is a short period of time captured in Connect between the Queue and the time it was put into the system.  For this reason, an IVR Leg is included on those experiences.

Different metrics align to each leg.  For example, the Offered Cnt only occurs on the QUEUE leg as it relates to the QUEUE, where as Handle Cnt only occurs on the AGENT leg since an AGENT has to take a call for it to be handled.

It is possible to see a callback with a direction of OUTBOUND.  In this case the original call was an OUTBOUND that the agent then transferred to a CALLBACK queue and then it proceeded through as a CALLBACK.

title: Handled Flag
description:
Values of 0 or 1.  Relevent information occurs on the AGENT leg type.  The handled flag indicates that the contact was handled by an agent.



In the callback situation, the system can connect to an agent and to the customers voicemail, this does not necessarily constitutes a handle.  Handle, as the business defines it, is when a customer and an agent interact.



This measure has a limitation for Callbacks that when the talk_dur+hold_dur>60 then the flag will be a 1.  Presumes that calls that go to voicemail will be less than a 1 minute and calls over 1 minute likely had the agent and the customer interacting.
